==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Schiller
<hw>Schil"ler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., play of
colors.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>The peculiar bronzelike luster
observed in certain minerals, as hypersthene, schiller spar, etc. It is
due to the presence of minute inclusions in parallel position, and is
sometimes of secondary origin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Schiller spar</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>an altered
variety of enstatite, exhibiting, in certain positions, a bronzelike
luster.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schillerization</ent>⟦br⟧
